{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"PROVEN ROOT CAUSE (two independent investigators converged + deterministic local proof):\n\nThe verify-identity whole-store gate fails because 206 validly-signed events were compacted into SNAPSHOT authorship_ledgers with position.commit_sha=NULL. This is exactly the CI count ('206 key-not-valid-at-era'; the store has exactly 206 null-commit signed ledger entries + 3 with a real commit = CI's '3 verified' ledger bit).\n\nMECHANISM (verify_authorship.py):\n1. The null commit_sha is baked into 30 snapshots ALL compacted BEFORE 4cc3ffbbb (14:34, 2026-07-17) added the resolve fallback to _build_authorship_ledger. 4cc3ffbbb is forward-only and never backfilled existing snapshots, so the nulls persist.\n2. At gate time the null is re-resolved via resolve_position_commit (a per-entry 'git log --diff-filter=A -- *POS*.json', WITHOUT --full-history and NOT using the batched --full-history map that LIVE events use via build_introducing_commit_map). This resolver is topology-dependent.\n3. When it returns None, the entry FAIL-CLOSES TWICE: _is_enforced(None)=True (ENFORCED, verify_authorship.py ~269) AND null-commit skips the era check -> any-key verify (real rebar-bot key) -> key_not_valid_at_era (~210-221). => enforced-not-verified => exit 1.\n4. Signer is the Rebar Bot identity 594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d (one ed25519 key from genesis CREATE, ZERO KEY_ADD events) - era validity itself depends on resolving the genesis CREATE position.\n\nDETERMINISTIC PROOF: forcing commit_sha=None on a real ledger entry -> classify=key_not_valid_at_era, _is_enforced=True (enforced fail). Resolving to the real pre-anchor commit -> classify=verified, _is_enforced=False (grandfathered).\n\nINTERMITTENCY: resolve_position_commit's result depends on the exact tickets-branch topology/CI git object-store state at run time. Same commit 95cbc7bb4 passed its own gate at flip time (fresh anchor) and failed on recheck 8h later - and some enforcement runs pass while others fail. I could NOT reproduce the None locally at the CI-era tip 4e87fa157 (git 2.55.0, non-shallow) - it resolves fine here - which pins the None to CI's git environment (repack/commit-graph/maintenance). This is why the 'fixes landed / whole-store gate proves it' precondition was false: the pre-merge gate at flip time sees ~0 post-anchor events so it cannot detect a topology-dependent failure that only appears as the branch grows.\n\nFALSIFIED: the COMPLETION_VERDICT sidecar theory - under 95cbc7bb4 those unsigned live sidecars are dropped at verify_authorship.py:349 (not in KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES) and never reach classification; rec-0000 has no SNAPSHOT and compaction excludes unsigned/non-KNOWN types. Not a contributor.\n\nDEFECT LEGITIMACY: real defect. verify-identity.yaml + the code comments state pre-enforce_since events are 'reported but never fail the gate', and verify_authorship.py:512-517 calls these entries 'validly-signed'. Force-failing a validly-signed, pre-anchor, otherwise-verifiable event violates both contracts.\n\nFIX DIRECTIONS: (A) code: give ledger re-resolution the same --full-history batched map live events use (kills the topology fragility + the O(n*2s) ~57min slowness); (B) don't fail-close a validly-signed unresolvable entry to enforced+kmva (grandfather or verify-against-current-keys); (C) data: backfill the 206 null commit_shas via recompact/repair. A+B are the durable code fix; C removes the latent data."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784337781797453001,"uuid":"9ded8ad3-426e-41b3-815d-debe1289e4d9"}